The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for recognizing attributes of objects and their parts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel Concept Sharing Network (CSN) for part attribute recognition, which involves deep learning techniques and optimization algorithms, making it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the problem of data insufficiency and proposes a solution that involves learning from mixed labels, which is relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its proposed method on various datasets, including human attribute datasets, which makes it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of its method for zero-shot part attribute recognition, which is relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
